445
00:22:31.180 --> 00:22:34.440
It's a subject dear to my heart, as I recently completed my

446
00:22:34.500 --> 00:22:35.200
PhD

447
00:22:36.080 --> 00:22:39.300
on perceived and actual adult water

448
00:22:39.360 --> 00:22:41.100
competencies in open water.

449
00:22:42.649 --> 00:22:46.620
And the evidence consistently shows that people

450
00:22:46.680 --> 00:22:48.700
tend to underestimate the risk

451
00:22:49.520 --> 00:22:53.330
and overestimate their ability to cope if something

452
00:22:53.360 --> 00:22:54.100
goes wrong.

453
00:22:55.280 --> 00:22:58.960
And this applies to both boating competence and water competence.

454
00:23:00.480 --> 00:23:03.020
People often believe that they can swim,

455
00:23:04.800 --> 00:23:06.440
that the conditions are manageable-

456
00:23:06.900 --> 00:23:07.240
Mm-hmm

457
00:23:07.920 --> 00:23:09.750
