458
00:23:10.640 --> 00:23:14.560
or that they will have time to put their lifejacket on if

459
00:23:14.640 --> 00:23:15.140
needed.

460
00:23:16.840 --> 00:23:20.390
But many boating incidents involve sudden and

461
00:23:20.440 --> 00:23:24.260
unexpected immersion where there is little or no time to respond.

462
00:23:25.480 --> 00:23:28.750
And that is why the key determinant of survival is whether the lifejacket is

463
00:23:28.820 --> 00:23:30.120
already being worn.

464
00:23:31.340 --> 00:23:35.240
The research shows that it doesn't make sense to leave it up to the skipper

465
00:23:35.940 --> 00:23:39.880
to determine whether the risk is great enough to don a lifejacket in

466
00:23:39.890 --> 00:23:42.440
