471
00:23:58.520 --> 00:24:02.020
challenges as somebody from a five-meter vessel: cold water

472
00:24:02.120 --> 00:24:05.590
shock, disorientation, fatigue, and

473
00:24:05.700 --> 00:24:09.620
difficulty staying afloat. So simple and consistent

474
00:24:09.720 --> 00:24:13.320
rules reduce reliance on judgment and interpretation

475
00:24:13.960 --> 00:24:17.320
in environments where some people are already prone to

476
00:24:17.380 --> 00:24:21.240
underestimating the risk. So that is why we support a clear

477
00:24:21.360 --> 00:24:25.140
behavior-based approach. If the vessel is moving, the

478
00:24:25.180 --> 00:24:29.000
lifejacket is on for all recreational vessels.

479
00:24:29.780 --> 00:24:30.190
Ngā mihi.

