549
00:28:25.968 --> 00:28:29.848
We represent about 175,000 license holders, anglers, and game

550
00:28:29.888 --> 00:28:33.828
bird hunters who spend a significant amount of time on or near New

551
00:28:33.868 --> 00:28:37.468
Zealand's lakes and rivers. Many of our license holders use

552
00:28:37.788 --> 00:28:41.648
small recreational vehicles, typically under six meters, while fishing for

553
00:28:41.688 --> 00:28:45.508
trout on inland lakes. Fish and Game supports the Life Jackets for

554
00:28:45.588 --> 00:28:49.308
Children and Young Persons Bill. Improving water safety is a goal we

555
00:28:49.368 --> 00:28:53.068
share. We also support the committee's consideration of extending the

556
00:28:53.087 --> 00:28:56.768
scope to include adults on recreational vessels under six meters,

557
00:28:57.208 --> 00:28:59.748
and we're comfortable with that extension in principle.

558
00:29:00.688 --> 00:29:01.808
What we ask today is that

559
00:29:02.968 --> 00:29:06.768
the committee consider two drafting matters that, if not addressed, would create

560
00:29:06.788 --> 00:29:10.488
practical problems for a significant proportion of our license holders.

561
00:29:10.548 --> 00:29:13.098
These are not objections to the intent of the legislation.

562
00:29:13.208 --> 00:29:16.788
They are refinements to ensure that the law works as

563
00:29:16.828 --> 00:29:17.438
intended.

564
00:29:18.928 --> 00:29:22.528
Points for the committee's consideration is, number one, is the

565
00:29:22.588 --> 00:29:26.558
definition of while underway. A large proportion of our license holders

566
00:29:26.668 --> 00:29:29.568
spend much of their time on the water, fresh water, that is.

567
00:29:29.708 --> 00:29:30.688
We don't have any

568
00:29:32.528 --> 00:29:34.888
statutory obligation over salt water, just fresh water.

569
00:29:36.268 --> 00:29:39.828
They spend a large portion of their time on the water anchored or

570
00:29:39.888 --> 00:29:43.428
drifting slowly or trolling at speeds under two knots.

571
00:29:44.078 --> 00:29:47.488
These are very low risk activities, and treating them the same as active

572
00:29:47.568 --> 00:29:51.148
navigation at speed would be disproportionate and impractical.

573
00:29:52.128 --> 00:29:55.888
We recommend that the definition of while underway explicitly

574
00:29:55.948 --> 00:29:59.228
exclude electronic anchoring, physical anchoring,

575
00:29:59.628 --> 00:30:01.988
drifting, and vessel movement under two knots.

576
00:30:02.648 --> 00:30:06.488
This is a straightforward fix that would protect safety conscious, law

577
00:30:06.508 --> 00:30:09.408
abiding anglers from unintended consequences.

578
00:30:10.568 --> 00:30:14.408
We also note that unpowered vessels under six meters would not benefit from the

579
00:30:14.468 --> 00:30:16.748
same exclusion we recommend for powered vessels.

580
00:30:17.368 --> 00:30:20.348
This is because these are generally smaller than powered vessels.

581
00:30:21.068 --> 00:30:24.468
We support the wearing of life jackets while underway for both adults and children

582
00:30:24.508 --> 00:30:28.448
on unpowered craft, as their smaller size presents a genuine

583
00:30:28.508 --> 00:30:31.308
safety risk with no equivalent low speed mitigation.

584
00:30:32.108 --> 00:30:35.758
We flagged this simply to ensure the distinction is deliberate and

585
00:30:35.868 --> 00:30:39.256
clearly expressed in the drafting.To

586
00:30:39.296 --> 00:30:42.776
summarize, Fish and Game supports this bill and supports extending its

587
00:30:43.176 --> 00:30:46.976
scope to include adults. The two matters I have raised are not objections,

588
00:30:47.056 --> 00:30:50.916
they're practical requirements to ensure the legislation does not inadvertently

589
00:30:50.936 --> 00:30:54.116
capture low-risk fishing activity.

590
00:30:54.176 --> 00:30:58.096
